Package: seqtrie
Title: Radix Tree and Trie-Based String Distances
Version: 0.2.4
Date: 2023-8-30
Authors@R: c(
    person("Travers", "Ching", email = "traversc@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
    person("Martin", "Moene", role = c("ctb", "cph"), comment = "span-lite C++ library")
	)
Description: A collection of Radix Tree and Trie algorithms for finding similar sequences and calculating sequence distances (Levenshtein and other distance metrics). Existing literature on computing distance with Trie algorithms: "Fast and Easy Levenshtein distance using a Trie" (2001) <http://stevehanov.ca/blog/index.php?id=114>, "Fast string correction with Levenshtein automata" (2002) <doi:10.1007/s10032-002-0082-8>, "Spell Checker Application Based on Levenshtein Automaton" (2021) <doi:10.1007/978-3-030-91608-4_5>.
License: GPL-3
Biarch: true
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
LazyData: true
SystemRequirements: GNU make
LinkingTo: 
    Rcpp, RcppParallel, BH
Imports: 
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.18.3), RcppParallel (>= 5.1.3), R6
Suggests:
    knitr, rmarkdown, stringdist, stringfish, qs, dplyr, Biostrings, igraph, ggplot2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
